
[1]piperin

   PIP'ERIN, n. A concretion of volcanic ashes.

   1. A peculiar crystalline substance extracted from black pepper. The
   crystals of piperin are transparent, of a straw color, and they assume
   the tetrahedral prismatic form with oblique summits.
